### plural executive (cont) ###

legislative powers
    veto
        the governors power to turn down legislation
        line-item
            only for appropriations
                authorizes gov to spend money in a specific way
        post-adjournment
            after legislature adjourns
            congress cant override

judicial powers
    judges are elected
    gov appoints replacements to vacancies
    clemency power (aka pardon)
        power to issue pardons
        pardons granted on recommendation of board of pardons and parole


more positions
    attorney general
    texas commissioner of agriculture
    comptroller of public accounts
        directs collection of tax and nontax revenues
        estimates evenues for the budgeting process
        certifies appropriations bills for passage